The paper deals with the problem of distilling a secret key from correlated variables obtained through a quantum key distribution protocol. This involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The construction presented in the paper involves using a classical channel to reconcile the key, which falls under the category of communication complexity (cs.CC). The paper also deals with the case of Gaussian variables, which falls under the category of mathematical modeling (cs.MM) and control systems (cs.SY).
